{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 33,
  "title": "第三十三章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "知人者智，自知者明。"
    },
    {
      "text": "勝人者有力，自勝者強。"
    },
    {
      "text": "知足者富。"
    },
    {
      "text": "強行者有志。"
    },
    {
      "text": "不失其所者久。"
    },
    {
      "text": "死而不亡者壽。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "知人者，智而已矣，未若自知者超智之上也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "勝人者，有力而已矣，未若自勝者無物以損其力，用其智於人，未若用其智於己也。用其力於人，未若用其力於己也。明用於己，則物無避焉，力用於己，則物無改焉。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "知足自不失，故富也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "勤能行之，其志必獲，故曰强行者有志矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以明自察，量力而行，不失其所，必獲久長矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "雖死而以為生之道不亡，乃得全其壽，身沒而道猶存，況身存而道不卒乎。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
